<span id="freeTextContainer5683695849543242761">Could Art and Religion be compatible? This book tells us the story of a little boy named Asher Lev, a Hasidic Jew who develops an extraordinary artistic sense from 4. Unfortunately for his parents, who are very believers and his community, it is only a vice that he must combat in order not to &quot;fall&quot; in the other world. It is, therefore, a real heartbreak for Asher, and it is exciting/interesting to follow the journey of this child and then this adolescent.</span>
  <span id="freeText5683695849543242761" style="display:none">Could Art and Religion be compatible? This book tells us the story of a little boy named Asher Lev, a Hasidic Jew who develops an extraordinary artistic sense from 4. Unfortunately for his parents, who are very believers and his community, it is only a vice that he must combat in order not to "fall" in the other world. It is, therefore, a real heartbreak for Asher, and it is exciting/interesting to follow the journey of this child and then this adolescent.</span>
